    <h2>About Guy Tillim</h2>
 

  <p>Tillim was born in Johannesburg in 1962 and completed a BCom at UCT in 1985. He started photographing professionally in 1986 and joined Afrapix, a collective of South African photographers with whom he worked closely until 1990. His work as a freelance photographer in South Africa for the local and foreign media included positions with Reuters between 1986 and 1988, and with Agence France Presse in 1993 and 1994. Tillim has received many awards for his work including a Mondi Award for photojournalism in 1998 and the Prix SCAM (Societe Civile des Auteurs Multimedia) Roger Pic in 2002. In 2003 he was awarded the Higashikawa Overseas Photographer Award in Japan. His work has been included in numerous exhibitions of South African art and photography, both in South Africa and internationally.</p>

